It is in the anticipation of enjoyment that
true & permanent happiness is to be
found, it is the ideal future pleasure
which is perpetually modified
by new feelings & enlarged by
the consoling [deletion][unclear]x[/unclear][/deletion] effect of slight
gratifications - How strongly the
mind may be worked up by
the feelings of [deletion]actual enjoyment[/deletion] imagination
& anticipated enjoyment is evident
from the strong emotion produced
by the touch of a beloved
person, or from a Kiss which
produces no physical pleasure
In this case it is evident
that all the pleasure is
imaginative, ie it coalesces at
the moment with pure impression -
.- & becomes supposed real
pleasure .- In cases where disgust
is produced by enjoyment, the [unclear]/[/unclear]

